Title: 4.0 out of 5 stars
Review: I tried several brands of this kind of product, and I would love this set the best, because it has two sheets of stickers, instead of only one in the other brands.  It also has an extra panel in the middle, for extra space on the scene, although the back and front sides are not as useable for sticker scenes as the other ones.  The main reason this is not my favorite of them all, is that the stickers are too hard to remove from the scene and reposition.  I nearly ripped the sticker trying to get it off the scene.  Also, the detail is a bit too fine, as the tails and legs are very thin, and I can see little kids ripping them off pretty easily. If they would get just a little less cut out, and leave a little more of the material around the edges, and a little easier to remove, this set would be a clear winner.  As is, I think with a lot of careful adult supervision, a 4-7 year old would have a lot of fun with this.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: My 21 month old loves it.

Title: 3.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Cute animal set, but my little one tore quite a few stickers trying to remove. Not sure I would recommend this one

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: These kept my child entertained on a flight for at least an hour , great buy !

Title: 3.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Too much adhesive and grandson cut his finger pulling a sticker off the board. The clear coating is also pulling away because of the adhesive. Waited my money.

Title: 2.0 out of 5 stars
Review: I was looking for something for my toddler to be able to play with and saw these. Nice idea but when you get stuff online you never know how it looks like in reality. I scrolled the pictures- saw two kids near glass doors and thought that these stickers are nice and big. However, when I got the package I was disappointed- a lot of tiniest stickers that can easily be swallowed and lost. Nothing even close to what it was presented like! So before you buy these, reconsider.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review:
Kids love stickers! Having a sticker book to peel and restick again and again gives us mamas a moment back in their day. My son is vehicles obsessed so this set was perfect with all different kinds of vehicles to talk about and name. Even introduced some new ones to him like submarines and blimps!
Of course once the stickers got really dirty they were unable to stick anymore. But extremely fun while it lasted!

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: These are really fun. You get so many stickers and they are ready high quality. They kept my toddler busy in 14 hour flight. I reused them atleast 5-6 times more after removing them. I would love to buy more if they have different sets.

Title: 1.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Paper thin. Child brought to show me and it immediately ripped down the seams.

Title: 1.0 out of 5 stars
Review: My son was very excited and play with it all day but the materials were not good and strong enough to be played with more than a day! Tails of most animals got reiped.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: These are great to keep in the car for short or long trips. Perfect for little hands to manipulate, Bright, colorful pages to put the reuseable stickers on. Good product.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: This is a super fun reusable sticker book. My 4 year old and my 9 year old both enjoy playing with it. They invent stories and use their imagination. The ability to reuse the stickers over and over is such a great thing. Great quality puffy stickers. Nice laminated cardboard book. Great gift. Good quality.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: I got this for my nieces and nephews to play with when they come over. They LOVE stickers and they LOVE this book! It’s something that keeps them entertained but we can also stop in the middle and come back to it. We all love that the stickers are reusable -they like to be able to move them around and I like that it doesn’t use up all the stickers for the next round of kiddos. None of us have trouble resticking them. It’s easy to wipe off if things spill on it. The younger kiddos also like that there’s “texture” to the stickers and even though they can’t really help put on the stickers they can help hold them and enjoy feeling them. Thinking I need to get some of the other scenes for them to have fun with!

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: My 2-3 year old toddlers are loving these. We love that they can restick on the scenery. It’s great for imaginative play. It comes with so many stickers I actually held a bunch back to make the stickers last even longer. Great for rainy days or when you need your kids to play quietly at a restaurant. Great quality!

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Our two year old loves these reusable sticker sets. She likes to sit at the table and play with them for a long time. When I first at open them, I remove the stickers one at a time and tell her what they are.  I talk to her about them as she places on the mat. She reuses them and talks about the stickers in her own language from there.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Fun way of teaching my son vehicle identification. He loves stickers and this even included a road to stick the cars on.

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: This book is awesome! You can fold it up and it has a handle for easy carrying. The stickers are puffy stickers and you get a ton to choose between. They are reusable so you can move them around and create different scenes. Great for in the car activities for the kiddos!

Title: 5.0 out of 5 stars
Review: Perfect little puff stickers and sticker book. My toddlee loves playing with this.

I consider myself a sticker book professional at this point and these stickers are made with the utmost quality. The stickers are thick and so puffy they are almost 3D.
